  "@type": "Article",
  "dateModified": "2026-03-06",
  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "Release notes are documentation that describes what changed between one version of a system and the next. They serve readers who already use the system and need to know what\u0026rsquo;s different — new features, fixed bugs, changed behavior, removed capabilities, and required actions.\nRelease notes sit at the intersection of technical writing and audience awareness. Their readers are not learning the system for the first time; they have existing mental models and workflows. The release notes must tell these readers what changed, why it changed, and what they need to do about it — without requiring them to relearn the entire system.\n",
